def: Of or pertaining to a pyrrhic, or to pyrrhics; containingpyrrhic; as, a pyrrhic verse.
Abounding with thyme; fragrant; as, a thymy vale. Akenside.Where'er a thymy bank he found, He rolled upon the fragrant ground.Gay.
To change the mind of (one's self). [Obs.]
Of or pertaining to the Tunguses; as, the Tungusic dialects.
Any species of turbellarian worms belonging to Planaria, andmany allied genera. The body is usually flat, thin, and smooth. Somespecies, in warm countries, are terrestrial.
To confine; to contract; to stringe. [Obs.]
